    <abstract>
      <t>&lt;p&gt;This document describes the NBMA Next Hop Resolution Protocol (NHRP).  NHRP can be used by a source station (host or router) connected to a Non-Broadcast, Multi-Access (NBMA) subnetwork to determine the internetworking layer address and NBMA subnetwork addresses of the "NBMA next hop" towards a destination station. [STANDARDS-TRACK]&lt;/p&gt;</t>
